Silenda is waiting here nervously

Theres just a few foot steps behind him before a tap on his shoulder. Freila wasn’t excited for this meeting of Silenda. But considering he was trying to make up for his mistakes, its a necessary one. Freila shuffled alittle in her place as she awaited Silenda to talk to her. What was she even gonna say to him?

He was startled but quickly calmed himself as he turned around. The second he saw her he nearly started to cry. he had to take deep breaths to stop himself from crying. "Hi..uh....F-Freila was it...?" He sounded so nervous....

The sound of his voice, and the loss of composure he got when he turned around  made Freila just a bit more at ease with him. She just looked up at him. Her voice was much more calm than she actually was. “ Yeah. Thats me. Of course, you’re Silenda...im hoping.” In reality, she was somewhat petrified. Someone who could kill her any second. It terrified her. But she kept her ground.
"Y-yes.....Im Silenda.." He smiled a bit "Do....you wanna sit down??? Also uh, I brought some snacks....if you want some...." He took off the bag he was wearing and held it up

“oh! No thank you.. i guess we can go sit down.” Freila just nods a bit as she walked over to a bench and motioned Silenda to follow her. She was still wary of him though. Still, she decided to be at least a bit softer.
He nodded and followed her "Uh....so how have you been..? Are you doing ok...?" He was bouncing his leg a bit

“Im uhm..doing fine. Its good to see you..sort of.” Freila just leans back on the bench as she looks over to Silenda. Looking as nervous as you would expect. How long has it been since she last saw him? Still, she just thought for a bit.

"Thank you....for meeting with me...I really appreciate it..." He smiled a bit "I....would like to show you the timeline that changed my heart one day.....I...think you'll like it...." He chuckled a bit

“I can tell...sort of..” Freila just looked over to him, Silenda wanting to show freila the timeline that changed him in this way. “ Ah...if its made you change this much, im sure it’ll be great,” She just nodded a bit, giving a small smile.
He was starting to relax more now. "So....Have you made friends in the void?" He asked

“Of course. Bucellati, Narancia, giorno, mista..hell, maybe even fugo..i’m so glad i get to talk to them.they’re the best. Im so lucky to have them as my friends.” [ She just smiles a bit, remembering the good and sometimes bad times shes had with the group. ]
He smiled "Thats really good to hear! Im glad you have such good and trustworthy friends." His til wagged a small bit which he quickly noticed and held it still, embarrassed

She didnt seem to notice, but just nodded and smiled at Silenda. “Thank you.” She thought for a moment before remembering. “Oh right, i still wanted to see the timeline that changed your whole perspective.”
He stood up "Follow me then...!" He smiled
Freila just nodded, standing up as well and gave a small gesture to tell him that she would be following.
Off to #portal-zone

"So, uh-"
Somnus rests her free hand on the side of her face and looks down, blinking at Seiko.
"...Nice, uh... weather, I think."
"Yes, it's a very lovely day today," she hums, looking around. "In all the growth of the void that I've missed, I'm glad there's at least *something* I can recognize."
"Were you not allowed outside?"
"I *was,* but chose not to go. I was always under strict surveillance— No privacy ever. It seems the ones who kept watch over me have forgotten, with recent events.."

"That sounds vile."
She pauses and bends down to look at a bug, poking at it.
"Are you, uh, alright?"
"Of course," she hums, sitting on the ground and looking at the same bug. "Besides, if I weren't alright, I wouldn't exactly have much to be motivated for."

"Well, what I mean is-"
She lets the bug crawl into her finger, holding it up for closer examination.
"...That kind of environment, it's not good for, uh, development. Fucks your brain up or something."
"I was over *two million years old*, Somnus," she hums, tilting her head in light curiosity at the insect. "I had already done my developing. My job from then on was to keep sane."

"It seems to me that, uh... development isn't something that you just *finish.* It seems like an... all the time thing. Like a constant."
She holds the bug out to Seiko, inviting her to let it crawl on her hand.
"We don't just... spin ourselves a cocoon and come out as an emotionally stable moth, I think."
"Of course not. We're always growing, always learning," she continues, holding her hand out and letting the bug crawl onto it, "But I already got passed the toughest part."

"...That is admirable, I think."
She takes a small, disposable camera from her pocket and starts fussing with it, trying to get it to focus on the insect.
"Being able to come out of that and still have your attitude- it's... nice."

She nods, holding up the bug to Somnus' camera. "Yes. Though, it was easy for me. I had a *very* good group of support, and even after I was cut off from them, I went on knowing someday the council would be taken down."

She adjusts her angle and snaps a few pictures, flipping through them.
"That's... lovely, really. You did better than I would've, I think."

"Well, to be fair, you didn't exactly have the, uh.. *best* situation."
She bends up a knee, resting her wrist on it so her hand can be held up limply. "Yes, everyone has their own life, and they're the ones who choose what to do with it, but.. Sometimes, people don't come from places that allow them to know that. So they don't know what else to do."

She nods, and offers her hand out for the bug.
"Shit just... sucks sometimes."

She carefully hand the bug over to Somnus, nodding. "Unfortunately. However!" she suddenly lights up, flashing Somnus a bright smile. "As long as we hope for and nurture these people, I'm *positive* we can set them on better paths!"

The insect flies away, and Somnus looks at Seiko, returning the smile.
"That's cute. Uh- it's nice, I mean. The idea- like, the sentiment of it. It's..."
She blinks.
"...Neat."
She nods. "Yes, it's *very* neat. Though, most of this is probably just coming from motherly instinct," she chuckles holding a finger up to her cheek sheepishly.

"... Mhm."
That's *adorable.* She really acts like this? Like, all the time?
"That's ... really sweet."
"I suppose it is," she hums in agreement, before standing up and *almost* loosing her balance, but not quite. "Is there anywhere else that's okay to go to?"
"Hmm? Like, other than the park? I, uh, don't have a *house,* or I'd offer to take you there- we could get ice cream, I guess?"

"Ooo, ice cream sounds wonderful!"
She clasps her hands together, smiling at Somnus with (barely hidden) excited joy.

"Niiice."
She stands, brushing herself off.
"I think know a place, uh- we can warp there now, if you want?"
"Mm.. No, let's walk again, I need the exercise!" she chooses, holding up hed arms and jokingly flexing them.

She nods, chuckling quietly.
"Uh, sounds like a plan."
She offers her hand to Seiko, leaning down a little.

She doesn't take Somnus' hand, instead quickly  holding onto her shoulder to give her balance as she goes on her toes, kissing Somnus' cheek before letting herself fall again and *actually* take her hand.

She flushes, blinking rapidly and setting a hand on her own cheek. *She just-*
"You- uh- thank you? I mean-"
How does she *respond* to that?
"Uh- that was... thanks?"
"You better get used to that," she teases with a small wink (;D)

"I..."
She puts her free hand over her face, peering out from between the fingers.
"Uh, I think... I think I could. Get used to it, I mean,"
She mumbles.
A loud laugh escapes her, and she practically bounces up and down. "You better!" she repeats, giving Somnus' hand another squeeze as she taps her foot against the ground happily.

She grins behind the hand, giggling and letting it drop from her face.
"Uh, yes ma'am. Shouldn't be *too* difficult."
"It *will* be, with all the love I'm going to shower you wish!" she exclaims, at this point hopping up and down excitedly.

She goes a brighter shade of pink, returning her hand to her face to hide her smile.
"You're very, uh, enthusiastic."
How is this woman *real?* And how is she interested in *Somnus?* She's like some sort of fucking... manic pixie dream milf; she belongs in a romantic comedy or something.
Her tail (which I totally didnt forget was a thing shut up) sways side to side excitedly. "Of course I am! Because I'm on a date with you! I'm *excited!*"

"I'm- I'm glad,"
Her tail swishes behind her, brushing along the ground.
"That you like it, I mean. Uh, the date."
She nods enthusiastically. "Are you?"

"Excited? I... I guess I am,"
She squeezes her hand.
"Uh, I have not been on a date in a very long time- or ever, maybe. I forget things."
She squeezes back. "But are you happy with the date? Have you liked it so far?"

She nods.
"Yeees- Waffle House is nice, and, uh- you are... pleasant to be around."

Her smile softens, satisfied with the knowledge that she's also a good date. "You are *also* very pleasant to be around! With everything that's been going on, this is the most relaxed I've been in a *while.*"

Her hand slides off her face and rests on the side of her cheek.
"That's kind of the *opposite* of what I typically, uh, go for,"
She chuckles,
"It's funny, I think."
"I suppose it is a little funny," she giggles, tilting her head to the side as she watches Somnus' hand movements carefully. "But the range is nice."

"Maybe I am... not good at being scary."
She taps her fingers against her face.
"Do *you* think I am? Scary, I mean?"
She shakes her head no, moving up to pap the sides of Somnus' hair. "You're very fluffy! I can not find you scary when you are so fluffy and cute."

She blinks.
"People keep saying that- *I* think it's intimidating. Like... the fucked up caterpillars that can sting you, or something."
"Well, fluffy can also equate with kitties! Or those really fluffy moths! Except you're much bigger. And more colorful."

"Thank you."
She uses her free hand to smooth down her collar a bit.
"Uh, people are scared of moths, I think."
